{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Just outside of Gainsville Texas
[F]I met and loved a girl named Alexis
[C]Long blonde hair the bluest eyes you've [G7]seen
[C]That woman loved me more than life
[F]Probably she'd still be my wife
[C]If I hadn't drank up [G7]all our plans and [C]dreams
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
She wanted a home lovin' man
[F]Not one that lived inside a beer can
[C]But some things never change and never [G7]will
[C]Love can't find a common ground
[F]But one of two can't settle down
[C]So I let her go but [G7]Lord I love her [C]still
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
So drink a toast to my Alexis
[F]She had a heart as big as Texas
[C]Raise your glasses and take your hats off [G7]please
[C]Set 'em up it's all on me
[F]This one's to the memory
[C]Of my sweet Alexis [G7]Gainsville Texas [C]queen
{end_of_verse}

